The propensity of people to acquire more favorable views about things to which they are repeatedly exposed, independent of their previous knowledge or experience with the subject. This occurs due to the psychological phenomenon of classical conditioning, in which a person gradually links a neutral stimulus with a favorable emotion. It implies that attitudes may be developed not just via conscious thinking or reasoning, but also through unconscious processes such as habituation and classical conditioning. This phenomena has a huge effect on how advertising, media, and social interactions affect us. 